0:
publish (Visual Studio)
Tools -> Command Line -> Developer command prompt
dotnet publish --runtime linux-arm64


1:
Install Pi os 64bit

2:
Install .Net 8.0
https://www.petecodes.co.uk/install-and-use-microsoft-dot-net-8-with-the-raspberry-pi/
wget -O - https://raw.githubusercontent.com/pjgpetecodes/dotnet8pi/main/install.sh | sudo bash

3:
Start raspberryPi
Install latest update

4:
sudo raspi-config
Advanced Options -> Wayland  select -> X11
Menu Preferences -> Raspberry Pi Config
Localisation -> Set Locale -> Amsterdam


5:
sudo nano /etc/xdg/autostart/myapp.desktop      -> Global
sudo nano /etc/xdg/lxsession/LXDE-pi/autostart  -> Per user (Working)

6:
Copy content-below in the opened autostart
Terminal Server: (Single file .Net app)
 
@lxpanel --profile LXDE-pi
@pcmanfm --desktop --profile LXDE-pi
@lxterminal --command "/home/pi/EcoHome/TestLinux"
@xscreensaver -no-splash


https://commandmasters.com/commands/lxterminal-linux/

7: Alternative
Terminal Server: (Multi file .Net app)

sudo nano /etc/xdg/lxsession/LXDE-pi/autostart

@lxpanel --profile LXDE-pi
@pcmanfm --desktop --profile LXDE-pi
@lxterminal -e /home/pi/EcoHome/EcoHome-Updater /home/pi/EcoHome/EcoHome.cfg
@xscreensaver -no-splash

echo 'export DOTNET_ROOT=$HOME/.dotnet' >> ~/.bashrc
echo 'export PATH=$PATH:$HOME/.dotnet' >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc


Reboot
-
==========================================================

Add the execution permission to a script:
sudo chmod +x /etc/init.d/myservice


